{
  "doc_id": "11841",
  "text": "In our framework we focus on the case of PCBs bioaccumulation in the Adriatic sea, a semi-enclosed basin characterized by high biodiversity [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] and by the presence of multiple contamination sources and anthropogenic perturbations. In the last decades different species of ecological and commercial interest have been surveyed in this region and several toxicological studies report the occurrence of PCBs bioaccumulation in the Adriatic sea [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] [CITATION_8] . We consider the PCBs bioaccumulation model presented in [CITATION_9] where a review of bioaccumulation studies in the North, Central and South Adriatic sea (period 1994-2002 ) is conducted in order to estimate bioconcentrations and PCBs flows among species. The model consists of 39 functional groups and is defined on top of a trophic reconstruction obtained from data collected in [CITATION_10] , one of the most complete quantitative studies of the Northern and Central Adriatic food web.",
